list_entry.display_value: Distribution: Feeds final consumers, installed outside substations
Generator: Steps-up voltage in power plants
Auxiliary: Feeds internal systems in substations
Excellent: unambiguous path or markers everywhere
Good: markers visible, sometimes require searching
Intermediate: few markers, path mostly visible
Bad: no markers, path sometimes invisible/pathless
Horrible: often pathless, some orientation skills required
No: pathless, excellent orientation skills required
Mostly Solid: gravel/rock with some soft material mixed in
Even mixture of hard and soft materials
Mostly Soft: soil/sand/grass with some hard material mixed in

list_entry.display_value: 0: Solid gravel/packed earth, no obstacles, wide curves
1: Some loose surface, small obstacles, wide curves
2: Much loose surface, large obstacles, easy hairpins
3: Slippery surface, large obstacles, tight hairpins
4: Loose surface or boulders, dangerous hairpins
6: Not rideable except by the very best mountain bikers
Deluxe (offers laundry or swimming pool, etc.)
No Road Markings or Traffic Signals
Diplomatic Mission of the Holy See
Use with caution: Uneven way, occasional difficult passages.
Difficult: Way narrow and exposed. May contain obstacles to step over and narrow passages.
Borderline: Passable only for experienced riders and horses. Major obstacles. Bridges should be examined carefully.
Dangerous: Passable only for very experienced riders and horses and only in good weather. Dismount.
Impassable: Way or bridge not passable for horses. Too narrow, insufficient support, obstacles like ladders. Danger of life.
In smoking areas, not physically isolated
Robust Wheels: trekking bike, car, rickshaw
High Clearance: light duty off-road vehicle
People displaced by disasters or conflicts
